# id: DefaultNettyHttpBinding -> protected String shouldUrlDecodeHeader(NettyHttpConfiguration configuration, String headerName, Object value, String charset) throws UnsupportedEncodingException
commentText: Decodes the header if needed to, or returns the header value as is.__@param configuration  the configuration_@param headerName     the header name_@param value          the current header value_@param charset        the charset to use for decoding_@return  the decoded value (if decoded was needed) or a <tt>toString</tt> representation of the value._@throws UnsupportedEncodingException is thrown if error decoding.
codeText: protected String shouldUrlDecodeHeader(NettyHttpConfiguration configuration, String headerName, Object value, String charset) throws UnsupportedEncodingException {_        _        if (Exchange.CONTENT_TYPE.equals(headerName)) {_            return value.toString()__        } else if (configuration.isUrlDecodeHeaders()) {_            return URLDecoder.decode(value.toString(), charset)__        } else {_            return value.toString()__        }_    }
